**Test plan (the four AC proofs):**
1. Live run: `etude run research` produces a manifest with exactly 5 stages whose
   output roles are findings/checked/draft/reviewed/toned and produced_by=original.
2. Capture-by-construction + chaining: fact-check input[findings].Artifact ==
   research output.Artifact (and the review gate attempt is recorded with
   status=pass, reviewing role=reviewed, seats include the registry stub + check).
3. Forward replay: `etude replay <run-id>` re-executes all 5 stages forward and
   reproduces the deterministic chain (byte-stable).
4. No-engine-change proof (structural; how the reviewer verifies): the bead diff
   adds NO non-test Go under internal/. The proof MUST be scoped to THIS bead's
   diff only — NOT the whole branch (the prior 5 beads legitimately added engine
   code). Reviewer runs, against this bead's working tree / commit relative to the
   etude-3a2 commit `6160230` (the pre-2pc.3 HEAD):
   `git diff --name-only 6160230..HEAD | grep -E '^internal/.*\.go$' | grep -v '_test\.go$'`
   (or `git status --porcelain` on the uncommitted 2pc.3 working tree) and expects
   EMPTY output for non-test internal Go — in particular nothing under
   internal/liverun, internal/cli, internal/workflow, internal/registry that is
   non-test. All added Go in THIS bead is `_test.go`; all other additions are under
   examples/ or docs/.

